The paper proposes a novel variational Bayes predictive coding RNN model for learning fluctuated temporal patterns. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and neural networks. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the proposed model. Additionally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories, as the paper discusses the development of different types of information processing and their implications for underlying neuronal mechanisms. Finally, cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible given the focus on maximizing the lower bound of the weighted sum of regularization and reconstruction error terms.
